{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はは}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=はは|-}}. {{IPAchar|/haha/}}: *{{IPAchar|/papa/}} → {{IPAchar|/fafa/}} → {{IPAchar|/fawa/}} → {{IPAchar|/fafa/}} → {{IPAchar|/haha/}}

Medial {{IPAchar|/f/}} {{IPAchar|[ɸ]}} regularly changes to {{IPAchar|/w/}} {{IPAchar|[ɰᵝ]}}, resulting in {{IPAchar|/fawa/}} → {{IPAchar|/hawa/}}, the expected final form; see ''hawa'' below. This form first appears in the {{w|Heian period}}. However, likely due to spelling influence or reduplication associations, the earlier {{IPAchar|/fafa/}} resurfaced in the late 16th century towards the end of the {{w|Muromachi period}}, with both forms seen until recent times, when ''hawa'' falls into disuse.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> Initial {{IPAchar|/f-/}} {{IPAchar|[ɸ]}} regularly becomes {{IPAchar|[h]|}}, resulting in modern {{IPAchar|[ha̠ha̠]}}.

